{"type":"message","id":"2e8f605a","parentId":"35882d5b","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:21:46.347Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is complaining that VibeSurf's browser is using too much memory. They're right - a normal browser on a host machine wouldn't use this much. The issue is that VibeSurf's Chrome runs with many additional processes (GPU process, utility processes for network/storage, renderer processes for each tab and extension, etc.) and combined with the fact that this is running in a container/VM with limited memory (only 3.7GB total), it easily gets exhausted.\n\nThe user is frustrated. Let me think about what we can do:\n\n1. The VibeSurf process itself (the Python process) is using 13.2% = ~489MB\n2. Chrome main process: 14.9% = ~551MB\n\n\n3. Multiple renderer processes are consuming significant memory as well\n\nWith 3.7GB total RAM on this machine, having multiple Chrome processes quickly becomes unsustainable. I could suggest the user install an MCP server with a lightweight browser, recommend a different approach for capturing the page like using their phone to share a screenshot, or ask them to share the page URL directly so I can fetch it another way. But really, they're running a full browser automation framework in a VM with tight memory constraints - that's the core issue. I should suggest killing VibeSurf and taking a simpler screenshot approach instead.\n\nActually, I could also try accessing the app directly since they're already logged in with their Feishu session - maybe I can fetch it as an external user or check if they have the cookies needed to bypass login. Though realistically, Feishu internal apps require authentication. Another option would be having them share the page screenshot through Feishu's built-in features rather than trying to capture it through the browser instance. But the most practical suggestion right now is to just have them paste a screenshot directly in the chat."},{"type":"text","text":"你说得对，正常宿主机开一个 Chrome 不会这样。问题在于这是沙盒里跑的，内存配额本身就小，VibeSurf 的 Chrome 架构又是多进程，每个扩展、每个标签都独立进程，加起来很容易撑爆。\n\n建议直接走简单路线——**你把那个应用页面截图发给我**。你在飞书里打开应用，按 PrintScreen 或者手机拍一张，粘贴过来就行。\n\n我看着图给你写前端代码，省时省内存。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776309684409,"responseId":"062f88b46a42365dbc51eb20b57761f3"}}
