{"type":"message","id":"575ccfcc","parentId":"b6cc465f","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:22:31.856Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying this isn't just a one-time thing - they'll need browser functionality later for product selection work too. So the memory issue with VibeSurf is a bigger concern.\n\nLet me think about this. The VibeSurf Chrome instance is taking too much memory. Maybe there's a way to configure it to use less memory, or use a lighter mode. Let me check if there are any configuration options.\n\nOr maybe the issue is that VibeSurf is running in a sandboxed environment with limited memory, and the user is running it on their own machine (host). Let me ask if they're running VibeSurf on the host or in the sandbox.\n \nWait, I need to clarify where VibeSurf is actually running - on the host machine or in this sandbox environment. If it's on the host, the memory constraints suggest something is off, since a single Chrome instance shouldn't be consuming 3-4GB of RAM. Let me ask to get more details about their setup. But actually, re-reading their message, they're saying running a browser on the server shouldn't consume much memory at all - which makes me wonder if VibeSurf is running on a totally different machine than I assumed. The Chrome process showing 14.9% of 3.7GB is roughly 560MB, which shouldn't cause these system memory issues, yet curl requests to the VibeSurf API are failing with exit code 28, indicating a connection timeout or failure to reach the host entirely.\n\nLooking at the memory breakdown more carefully - the system has 3.7GB total with only 112MB free and 829MB in buffer/cache, leaving just 210MB available. The Chromium process is the dominant memory consumer, but the real problem seems to be that VibeSurf itself (Python process) and multiple Chrome renderer processes are collectively exhausting available memory, causing the API to become unresponsive.\n\nI should probably recommend configuring VibeSurf to use fewer renderer processes or a lighter browser mode to avoid overwhelming the system."},{"type":"text","text":"明白，你后面还要用浏览器做选品，这个是长期需求。\n\n问题在于 VibeSurf 的 Chrome 默认开了很多进程（标签页+扩展+渲染器），在沙盒环境里容易把内存吃满。\n\n我可以帮你查一下 VibeSurf 有没有轻量模式配置，让 Chrome 少开些进程。你先告诉我——你是怎么启动 VibeSurf 的？命令行参数有哪些？我看看能不能优化它的内存占用。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776309729291,"responseId":"062f88e1f277013018f22f3455d02406"}}
