{"type":"message","id":"6d44ad50","parentId":"d7720a3d","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:26:41.361Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying VibeSurf is running inside a Docker container. That explains the memory issue - the container likely has limited memory allocated. The browser is running inside the container, not on the host. That's why it uses a lot of memory in a constrained environment.\n\nLet me think about this. If VibeSurf is in a container, the browser processes are running inside the container with its memory limits. The host machine (where the user is) would be accessing the browser through the container's exposed ports.\n\nBut the browser itself runs inside the container. The memory issue is because the container doesn't have enough memory allocated.\n\nHowever, the user's main goal is to clone the frontend of that Feishu app. They mentioned they need browser access later for product selection too.\n \nWait, the user's message is fragmented - they seem to be responding to something about the browser running inside Docker, possibly mentioning memory constraints or that they can't capture screenshots easily in this setup. Let me figure out what they're actually asking for."},{"type":"text","text":"Docker 容器里跑 VibeSurf 浏览器，这就解释了——容器内存配额有限，Chrome 多进程一跑就爆。\n\n你现在发的是截图还是视频？发过来吧，我看内容决定下一步。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776309991611,"responseId":"062f89e772171bca183d2b707c44bf80"}}
