{"type":"message","id":"fa93eeda","parentId":"ad961eda","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:26:57.383Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying VibeSurf was deployed inside a Docker container. That explains the memory issues - the container likely has limited memory. But they're saying it's already deployed that way. Let me understand their setup better.\n\nActually, the user is explaining why VibeSurf was slow/had memory issues - because it's running in a Docker container with limited resources. This is useful context.\n\nNow I still need to figure out the current situation - do they want to continue with the browser or use screenshots? They just sent a message saying VibeSurf is in a Docker container. I should acknowledge this and ask what they want to do next."},{"type":"text","text":"明白了，VibeSurf 跑在 Docker 里，内存受限。\n\n这个是长期问题，后续要用浏览器选品也会遇到这个瓶颈。\n\n**两个方向：**\n\n1. **调 Docker 内存限制** —— 给容器多分配点内存（比如 4G+），浏览器才能正常运行\n2. **绕过浏览器** —— 你把应用截图发我，我看图写前端，后续选品如果必须用浏览器，再单独解决\n\n你想先走哪条路？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776310007645,"responseId":"062f89f7dc057ae6cc7474b79273e46e"}}
