{"type":"message","id":"6428e368","parentId":"4239a3a2","timestamp":"2026-04-16T13:07:10.419Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I have PIL but not cv2. I can't extract frames from video without ffmpeg or cv2. Let me think about what to do.\n\nActually, I could try to use the `image_generate` tool to analyze the video, but it only handles images. \n\nActually wait - let me check if there's a way to get a frame from the video. Maybe I can use `exec` with a Python script that uses PIL to read the video... but PIL doesn't support video.\n\nLet me think differently. The file is 88MB which is quite large for a screen recording. Maybe I can use `strings` or some other tool to extract text from it, but that's not going to give me the visual UI.\n\nActually, let me check if there's a way to use the Agent Browser skill to help here, or if I can extract frames another way.\n\nWait - I should check if there's a node.js video handling library available. Or maybe I can use `curl` with a video frame extraction API if one exists.\n\nActually, the simplest approach: let me just check if there's a way to get a thumbnail/frame. The video was a screen recording of what appears to be the miaoda.feishu.cn app. But I don't know what's in it.\n\nHmm, let me try a different approach. Let me check if the file is actually a valid video and try to extract at least some frames using whatever tools are available.\n\nActually, let me just try to run the video through something that can analyze it. The `image_generate` model might be able to look at video frames if I can extract them. But I need ffmpeg.\n\nLet me check if I can install ffmpeg quickly or if there's another way."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_w572lxgk71pj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"apt-get install -y ffmpeg 2>&1 | tail -5","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"tot